'''Siriondil''' means "Devoted to [[Sirion]]" in [[Quenya]] (from ''[[Sirion]]'' and ''[[-ndil]]'', "friend, lover, devoted to"), and can refer to:
* [[Siriondil (King of Gondor)|Siriondil]] ({{TA|570}} - {{TA|830|n}}), the eleventh [[Kings of Gondor|King]] of [[Gondor]].
* [[Siriondil (son of Calimmacil)|Siriondil]] (died before {{TA|1945}}), son of [[Calimmacil]] and the father of [[Eärnil II]].
